commit.message:
audioio-forked-stream: do not use SIGKILL

On many current systems, the console gets messed up (user input
not visible), after running an ecasound session with mp3, ogg,
or other inputs where input is handled by piping data from another
process.

The rootcause seem to be ecasound's use of SIGKILL as the final
cleanup step to ensure no forked child processes are left behind.

This seems to cause more harm than good, so change the logic to just
do a SIGTERM in this case.
libecasound: class interfaces changed, bump ver to 25

libecasound: do not normalize float file outputs to [-1,1]

Ecasound has traditionally normalized sample data before
export to [-1,1] value range and not allowed samples above 0dBFS.

There's really no good reason for doing this, especially as
ecasound imports float audio files with values oer 0dBFS just
fine, so export should behave similarly.

This is a minimal patch to change the behaviour. There is a lot
of old cruft in samplebuffer.cpp that should be cleaned up, but
I resisted the temptation and kept this patch simple as possible.

build: fix check for LV2

The configure.ac fix in 2.9.3 to check for LV2 support missed
the case where --enable-lv2 option is not given at all. In
this case, the deprecated lv2core package names was still used
in the search and this will fail on newer systems. Fix this case
as well.
build: 2.9.3+dev tree open for development

build: 2.9.3 release

Update copyrights, remove Freshmeat from README (website no longer
maintained) set version to 2.9.3.

doc: update README, AUTHORS and RELNOTES for release

Change minimum version required for Python. Fix some spelling errors.
pyecasound: remove obsolete comment

pyecasound: style update to match with python3 conventions

Fix multiple style issues to make code closer to typical
python3 code (string literals, self object, indentation, etc).
doc: update RELNOTES for 2.10 release
doc: add David Runge to AUTHORS

rubyecasound: fix warning concerning Object#timeout

The Object#timeout method was deprecated in Ruby 2.3.0 and
following warnings was emitted for each ECI command:

ecasound.rb:133: warning: Object#timeout is deprecated, use Timeout.timeout instead.

Fix this by using Timeout.timeout interface instead.
doc: update NEWS

pyecasound: add support for python3.x

Update Python ECI implementation (ecacontrol.py) to support
Python3.x while still keeping compatibility with Python2.7.

pyecasound: remove C pyecasound implementation

The C implementation of ECI API using Python module interface
was deprecated in 2012 in 2.9.0. It has still been possible
to enable it with "--enable-python=iwantc".

With upgrade of Ecasound's Python support to Python 3.x,
the C pyecasound implementation would require further
updates to keep using it with the new Python3. Instead,
the C implementation is now dropped completely.
The pyeca.py implementation is mature and supports both
Python2.7 and Python3.

ecatools: further fixes to ecamonitor for python3 support

Fix issues discovered with more complete test runs with
python3.

libecasound: fix compiler warnings in eca-engine.cpp

GCC 8.3.0 warns about misleading indentation in the switch statements.
No functional impact, but fix this still to clarify the code.

libecasound: LADSPA: fix bug in parsing output capability

Fix an old bug in parsing LADSPA plugin hints on port
properties. The check whether a LADSPA port is an output or
not, was incorrect and was always set as false.

This bug did not prevent using LADSPA plugins with output
ports, but the ecasound description of the plugin (as e.g.
in output of "map-ladspa-list") was wrong.

Bug was found based on warning from GCC 8.3.0.

kvutils: return error from kvu_sleep() if platform support missing

In addition to emitting an error trace, also return error to caller
in case platform implementation is missing support for sleeping
(usleep, nanosleep and friends).

build: fix issue in configure.ac check for execvp()

Set language to C when doing checks for POSIX functions
such as execvp(). With some C++ compilers, the autoconf
generated tests generate fails despite function being
available.

build: update config.guess and config.sub to 2018-02

Update files from autotools-dev.

kvutils: fix compilation errors for nanosleep/usleep

Explicitly specify global namespace for POSIX calls
nanosleep() and usleep(). Without the explicit scope set,
compile error may result due to "using namespace std"
at start of file.

ecatools: ecamonitor updated to support python3

Upgraded ecamonitor to work with python3. Initial conversion
done with '2to3' tool with some manual modifications on top.
Ecamonitor still works with python2, but at least python2.7
is required.
build: do pkg-config search for lv2 instead of deprecated lv2core
doc: Fix incorrect link to git tree web interface

eca-chainsetup: remove inaccurate dbc warning in device open

A false design-by-contract (DBC) warnings was emitted when
opening a file or audio device that modified audio parameters
to closest matching value, but did not report
'locked_audio_format()==true'. This check is not valid as
modification of audio parameters is allowed even for objects
that do not have a locked audio format.
build: version to 2.9.2+dev, tree opened for devel
doc: final commit for 2.9.2, NEWS/RELNOTES/copyrights updated

build: do C++ builds in -std=c++98 mode by default

Codebase builds ok with -std=c++14, but it does not use any
features of C++11 or newer yet, and it does emit warnings in
C++11 mode (e.g. use of dynamic exception throw specifications).

Codebase will be migrated to C++11 later, but before that,
the obvious warnings at least need to be removed.

audioio_alsa: fix xrun error messages

Fix the overrun/underrun (xrun) warning message for ALSA PCM
devices. The the xrun duration has been miscalculated
incorrectly with all current versions of ALSA (ever since
clock_monotonic became the default for trigger tstamp).
